uk.ac.cam.darknet.backend

Class SpektrixCSVParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.cam.darknet.backend.SpektrixCSVParser

  • public class SpektrixCSVParser
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is a primary data collector with a graphical user interface allowing manual data input. It represents the primary way of entering data into the system. This collector supports reading comma-separated values (CSV) files generated by booking systems.
    Author:
    Farah Patel

        public java.util.List<Individual> loadfromCSV(java.lang.String pathname,
                                     int venue)
                                       throws java.io.IOException,
                                              java.sql.SQLException,
                                              java.text.ParseException
        Parses CSV file from Spektrix and produces a list of Individuals
        Parameters:
        pathname - path to Spektrix CSV file, CSV file expected to have the following format: Customer Id, First Name, Last Name, Email Address, Event Name, Event Date/Time, Seat, Price, Ticket Type, Date Confirmed, Sales Channel. Note ignores first line of CSV file on the assumption that this lays out columns and it not actual data
        venue - The ID of the venue at which the show is going to take place.
        Returns:
        List of Individuals stored in Database
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If CSV file not found or if read is unsuccessful
        java.sql.SQLException
        java.text.ParseException
